        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Thus the derivative of f at any rational number is ±1. Since f is continuously differentiable, we conclude that f ′ (x) = 1 for all real x or f (x) = −1 for all real x. Since f (O) must be an integer (a rational number with denom- inator 1), f (x) = x+n or f (x) = −x+n for some integer n.",
        "bbox": [
          0.556078431372549,
          0.19272727272727272,
          0.9192156862745098,
          0.2787878787878788
        ],
